thought.text:
`getEnd()` is defined on the `Node` class. But maybe there's a circular import issue where the `Identifier` class isn't fully resolved yet when `TypeArgumentedNode.ts` is processed, making TypeScript see a different `Identifier`.

Let me check what imports are in `TypeArgumentedNode.ts` imports - currently it imports `Node` from `../common`, and that might be circular. Let me look at the approach in `TypeParameteredNode.ts` to see how it handles this:

The `TypeParameteredNode.ts` has:
```typescript
function getInsertPos(node: TypeParameteredNode & Node) {
  const namedNode = node as any as (NamedNode & Node);
  if (namedNode.getNameNode != null)
    return namedNode.getNameNode().getEnd();
  else if (Node.isCallSignatureDeclaration(node) || Node.isFunctionTypeNode(node))
    return node.getFirstChildByKindOrThrow(SyntaxKind.OpenParenToken).getStart();
  else
    throw new errors.NotImplementedError(...);
}
```

They use `node as any as (NamedNode & Node)` - a cast through `any`. But they don't do a `getFirstChildByKindOrThrow(SyntaxKind.Identifier)`.

The issue might be that `getFirstChildByKindOrThrow` returns `KindToNodeMappings[TKind]` which, due to TypeScript module resolution with circular imports, maps `SyntaxKind.Identifier` to an incomplete `Identifier` type.

Let me try a different approach - cast the result to `Node`:

